	     <br clear=all><small>Posted @ Mon, Apr 5th 1:29 PM 2004</small></td></tr>
	     <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=239825><span id= >ArcaneRider</span></a><br><span id=notbold>138 posts<br><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Default [1.65]</td><td valign=top class=mform width=100%><p>&quot;Mages use T Rods, Necros Lich&quot;<br><br>agreed with this post, self regen completely negates trod damage, but id still go aego&gt;phantom armor anyway, esp. on raids.<br><br>its useful for both classes, im 57 and currently if i had this belt i wouldnt take it off for a while. on my server, most folks just have bloodweave from what ive seen. if this was in bazaar for 10k id definitely save for it.<br><br>for trod vs lich, dunno which is more efficient, but consider necro cant lich on horse (right?), trod + mount gives a lot of mana. with specialization conjur maxed, first trod charge completely replenishes all the mana spent casting, so thus extra 600 mana from 900HP over the course of the whole trod.<br><br>&quot;3 charges of 220mana for 300hp&quot;<br><br>are you sure? thought that was mod rod not myst rod, my lvl 56 rod takes 450 dmg and gives about 300 mana back.<br><br>as for pets, theres always pathing problems and poofing problems (velks..), just /pet guard, click, /pet follow. better than a resummon and a little faster than suspend (if you even have that, especially useful if you dont have suspend). plus pets sometimes path off in general, again, click and pop.<br><br><br>now stfu, this is a great item no matter what, if you can use the stats great (even if i had a better +mana belt the +hp on this is invaluable, not a lot of belts available to me with that much +hp), if you have a better belt then stash it in your clicky bag for later.</p>&nbsp;<br></td></tr>
